node.text:
Ahead of this weekend’s big race, the drivers of the @porsche Motorsport GT Team walk us through their training circuit in Aragon, Spain. With long straights that allow the drivers to reach up to 300kph in speed, the track is the ideal spot to test the unique aerodynamic kit specific for this race.

Check back this weekend to root the team on to victory!

node.text:
What an intense and rich year.
After celebrating 160 years of watchmaking, we look forward to the next 160!
Let’s go back to our biggest moments that made 2020.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TAG Heuer on September 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, ocean and text that says 'TAG HEUER'.

node.text:
Strapped in and ready to go!

With a newly developed adjustable clasp system cut-to-measure, the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 ensures professional surfer @kai_lenny has the freedom to accommodate his wetsuit and any other changing conditions that may make the wrist expand or contract.

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TAG Heuer on September 13, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing, ocean and text that says 'TAG HEUER'.
Photo by TAG Heuer on September 13, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and wrist watch.
Photo by TAG Heuer on September 10, 2021. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text:
Strapped for time? 

Not to worry - the new folding clasp design on the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 timepieces allows for micro-adjustments that are practical and easy to use, ensuring you are suited up and ready to relax.

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TAG Heuer on September 09, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, wrist watch and text that says 'TAG HETER'.

node.text:
Still waters run deep. 

On a journey beyond silence, at the edge of human ability, timing is everything. And only a reliable, pressure-proof tool watch, will have you prepared for any intense adventure, just like the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 Night Diver of @arthurguerinboeri. 

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TAG Heuer on September 08, 2021. May be an image of wrist watch and text that says '50 AQUARACER TA ー AUTOMATIC 40 31 20 08 3 TAG HEUER'.

node.text:
Glow up.

Different from other dive watches, the fully luminescent dial on the new #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 Night Diver is coated in green SuperLumiNova® on the hands and hour markers, delivering exceptional glow-in-the-dark performance and the ultimate legibility in extreme low-light conditions.

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.text:
Into the deep.

Far from the light, immersed in sub-zero temps, and outside the comfort zone. Free diver @arthurguerinboeri set a world record for the longest under-ice swim in a single breath with nothing but his #TAGHeuerAquaracer at his side.

How far would you go to see who you truly are?

Introducing the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 Night Diver. 

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TAG Heuer on September 01, 2021. May be an image of wrist watch, jewelry and text that says 'TAG HEUER'.

node.text:
Pushing the limits of style and action.

The slim 36 mm case on the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 combines brushed and polished steel that makes for a sturdy, yet stylish timepiece. 

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by TAG Heuer on August 29, 2021. May be an image of wrist watch.

node.text:
Forever raising the bar.

A graceful wavy pattern decorating the dial and a unidirectional turning bezel for accurate dive time measurement, the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 has all your bases covered. 
Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.text:
Versatility beyond belief.

On or off the court, the #TAGHeuerAquaracer Professional 300 is the watch of choice for tennis superstar @naomiosaka.

Discover more at the link in our bio.

node.text:
Thank you, @PatrickDempsey, for joining us for this iconic race weekend!

We had the privilege to go behind the scenes with Patrick and Alex Stehlig and witness the great work the teams did all weekend. Congratulations to all the teams for a brilliant race!

If you missed it, go in our highlights stories and discover how the race went!
